3 community improvement district may be effected only after approval by the
4 city or village having any zoning jurisdiction over such property.
5 Sec. 20. Whenever it shall be necessary, in making any improvement
6 under the provisions of the Community Improvement District Act, to enter
7 upon or cross any state or public lands, the community improvement
8 district shall have the right to acquire a right-of-way across the same
9 by the exercise of the power of eminent domain.
10 Sec. 21. (1) The community improvement district shall have the
11 power to annually levy a tax on the taxable value of the taxable property
12 in the community improvement district at an aggregate rate not to exceed
